<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<CONTENT id="_3793154_1"><TITLE value="Session 14"/><TITLECOLOR value="#000000"/><DESCRIPTION
   value=""/><BODY><TEXT>&lt;h4&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src="@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@bbcswebdav/xid-56620587_1" alt="" style="border: 0px solid #000000;"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src="@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@bbcswebdav/xid-56620545_1" alt="" height="576" width="740" style="border: 0px solid #000000;"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;h4&gt;Introduction&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;div&gt;The CIS (Center for Internet Security) Critical Security Controls are a prioritized set of actions for cybersecurity.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Thes controls form a defense-in-depth set of specific and actionable best practices to manage and deal with the most common cyber attacks&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;During this session we will examine the CIS controls&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h5&gt;News&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;More Aussi Telcos in trouble, &lt;a href="https://ia.acs.org.au/article/2025/dodo--iprimus-data-breach-sees-email-and-sim-cards-hacked.html?ref=newsletter&amp;amp;deliveryName=DM28782" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt;Dodo, iPrimus data breach sees email and SIM cards hacked | Information Age | ACS&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 10pt;"&gt;Global outage affecting Australia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt;. &lt;a href="https://ia.acs.org.au/article/2025/aws-outage-knocks-out-netflix--youtube--roblox.html?ref=newsletter&amp;amp;deliveryName=DM28782" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;AWS outage knocks out Netflix, YouTube, Roblox | Information Age | ACS&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 10pt;"&gt;Ongoing repercussions of a breach&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt;. &lt;a href="https://7news.com.au/news/crime/medibank-faces-second-class-action-over-russian-hacker-data-theft-c-10198300" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Medibank 2nd Class Action&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@bbcswebdav/xid-46884682_1" alt="" width="281" height="211" style="border: 0px solid #000000;"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Medibank faces second class action over Russian hacker data theft&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The health records of almost 10 million Australians were stolen in the attack, then dumped on the dark web.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;To followup the news article in Session 9, &lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://ia.acs.org.au/article/2024/how-to-get-a-job-in-cyber-security.html?ref=newsletter&amp;amp;deliveryName=DM24069" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;How to get a job in cyber security | Information Age | ACS&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; .&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;When you are nearing the end of your study, make you have a good read of this. &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a alt="" href="@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@bbcswebdav/xid-61370270_1" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;ACS-CareerGuide_Cybersecurity.pdf&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Not exactly news, but this might be of interest to some of you,&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a alt="" href="@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@bbcswebdav/xid-55108722_1" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Simplilearn AI in CyberSecurity.pptx&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h5 id="anonymous_element_24"&gt;Topic&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;div&gt;This is our last formal session for Security Essentials.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;We will conclude our investigation into the current cyber security frameworks (CSF).&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Specifically we will focus our attention on the Centre for Internet Security (CIS) controls for cyber security protection.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h5&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Out of Session Activity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;div&gt;Review the CIS controls, and think about how this framework compares to the others studied:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Cyber kill chain&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Essential 8&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;NIST&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div&gt;Read the article on the Medibank legal woes.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Now that we can look back on this, is there anything obvious in the cyber defence that should improved on?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h5&gt;Portfolio Tasks&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;div&gt;Check the assessments tab.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Complete and submit AT1 (Portfolio) &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PART-FIVE Essentials&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</TEXT><TYPE
